Schedule and Subscribe to Reports

Receive notifications that keep you informed about metrics you care most about without having to manually run reports. In Salesforce Classic, you can specify criteria that trigger report notifications.

You can subscribe yourself and other users, groups, or roles to receive refreshed report results by email on a schedule that you set. Set report conditions so that recipients are notified when a total in your Salesforce report reaches a meaningful threshold.

When subscribing to a report, choose to receive report results as a formatted spreadsheet (.XLSX) or a comma-separated (.CSV) file attached to the subscription email. You can also subscribe to get report notifications in Salesforce Classic.

Combine subscriptions, actions, and conditions in a single joined report that shows who set up each subscription, the schedule and conditions, and the recipients and actions.

Schedule Reports in Salesforce Classic
You can set up a report to run itself daily, weekly, or monthly and send the results automatically to the people who need them.
title: Schedule and Subscribe to Salesforce Reports
